caption: Got sandwiches to go. Noticed there was chewed gum in my sandwich when I got home. Called them to let them know. Long story short: Manager says “no one chews gum here. It’s on your end.”  Super cool.  Will never ever return.

I placed an online order for my company several days in advance. The order was for around 40 people. I called the store and spoke with the manager to ensure they'd have the order ready, and delivered on time. I called as a courtesy to make sure they would have the correct number of staff there on the day of the delivery. I was promised the order would be in my hands at 12:30pm today 2/5/2021. Not only was the order 30 minutes late on delivery time, but several of the orders were made incorrectly and did not have the names of the individuals on the orders for distributing them to the staff. I called to talk about this with the manager, and he made the excuses that they were too busy, and understaffed. YOU ARE THE MANAGER - I called you days in advance so you could schedule more people if you needed to! No excuse makes up for the embarrassment of not having lunch organized for our company event. The manager says he will be refunding the entire order - but this is an unacceptable level of customer service.

I placed an order at 12:35 p.m. and waited over an hour for it to be delivered.  I work literally 1 block from this location so why it took so long is not understandable. This was actually the second time I've had this experience with this JJ's location.  I chose not to voice a complaint the first time because I gave them the benefit of the doubt, figuring they were just slammed that day.  I'm totally done with JJ.  I ordered the Vito sandwich today and it was not good at all.  It was dry and very bland.  Don't plan on giving them another shot.

I was fired after he berated me for asking about **hazard pay** (which he bragged on Facebook about giving to his employees, then immediately took away) and then made personal insults about the death of my child’s father IN FRONT OF CUSTOMERS. Unfortunately, I’m not the only one with a story like this. Don’t work for JJs in Huntsville and eat somewhere where the owner cares about the little people.

I purchased a Club Tuna sandwich at this Jimmy John's location at 6:30pm on March 16th 2020.  At 4am the next day I had to go to the ER at Huntsville Hospital because I couldn't breathe.  The doctor informed me that I had a viral infection.  I cannot say for certain what I had, but I'm confident that something in this sandwich made me sick.  I am confident in saying that this sandwich made me sick because no other members of my family were sick despite us sharing every meal together for the last week.  I spoke with the owner of the franchise, Matthew Kritzer, and he said that without proof, he would do nothing for me.  I'm sure Matthew knows very well that Jimmy John's has a poor reputation for using tainted food products.  I will never be going back to this location, and I suggest others do likewise.
